comments: Abolished 1.10.1933 and added to the parish of Radcliffe.
Abolished 1894 and added to the parish of Birtle cum Bamford.

Abolished 1.10.1933 and divided between the parishes of Rochdale, 
    Heywood and Bury. See also Table 2, note (i).

Abolished 1.4.1974 and added to the Bury unparished area. 
    See also Table 2, notes (k) and (l).

That part which until 1894 formed part of the parish of 
    Hopwood. See also Table 2, note (e).

Abolished 1894 and divided between the parishes of Ramsbottom, 
    Bury, Tottington, Ainsworth and, Radcliffe.

That part which until 1894 formed part of the parish of Tottington Lower End. 
    See also Table 2, note (a).

Abolished 1894 and divided between the parishes of Heywood, Bury, 
    Birtle cum Bamford and Unsworth.

Created 1894 from the parts of the parishes of Heap, Hopwood, 
    Castleton, Pilsworth and Birtle cum Bamford, in Heywood Municipal Borough. 
    See also Table 2, notes (e), (f) and (h).
Abolished 1894 and divided between the parishes of Heywood, Middleton and Castleton by Rochdale. See also Table 2, notes (c) and (d).

That part which until 1894 formed part of the parish of 
    Hopwood. See also Table 2, note (c).

That part which until 1894 formed part of the parish of

Abolished 1894 and divided between the parishes of Whitefield,

See Table 2, note (h).

    See also Table 2, note (i).

    See also Table 2, note (h).

Abolished 1894 and divided between the parishes of Tottington,

Abolished 1.10.1933 and added to the parish of Ramsbottom.
